rdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>3/22/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>2:52:55 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.eternusastralis.com/site/logo/ea60x60.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">wiz epic info.</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">i took this from graffe's webpage for the wiz's who do not know how to do the wiz epic<br>
<br>
This quest is started by talking to Solomen within the Temple of Solusek Ro.<br>
 Solomen is a human wizard located on the left portion of the temple, third floor,<br>
 between the two undead knights, one room away from Lord Seafire. The end<br>
  result of the quest is not known, but it is thought to be a blunt sceptre type<br>
 weapon with fantastic stats as well as unique particle effects when held. This is<br>
                   the mother of all wizard quests.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
You say, 'hail Solomen'<br>
<br>
Solomen says 'Ah, I see you have found my study. This is where I study and scribe<br>
the history of magic in Norrath.<br>
<br>
You say, 'what history?'<br>
<br>
Solomen says 'I have worked to chronicle everything from the beginnings of magic<br>
to what we consider the modern day of magic. Solusek Ro has been very<br>
generous to those who wield magic in Norrath. But throughout history there is<br>
one thing I have noticed - too much power corrupts the soul. I have seen and<br>
documented that the strongest wizards and those closest to Solusek Ro become<br>
corrupted by their power.<br>
<br>
You say, 'what wizards?'<br>
<br>
Solomen says 'Unfortunately, I don't have time to speak of such things right now.<br>
But I could use your help since you are here. I have here an envelope that I need<br>
delivered to one Camin Rah. You can find Camin in the wizard tower in the city of<br>
Erudin. He is a sage like myself whose knowledge rivals my own. Do you [agree]<br>
to undertake my task? <br>
<br>
You say, 'I agree.'<br>
<br>
Solomen says 'Here you are, then. Good luck on your journey.<br>
<br>
<br>
Camin can be found at the Vasty Deep Inn within Erudin. To find him inside the Inn,<br>
open the front door to the Inn and go up the stairs on your right. Follow the hallway<br>
around the second floor and Camin is found behind the first door upon your left. Off the<br>
bat, he is normally indifferent or apprehensive to everyone. Hand him the note that was<br>
given to you by Soloman and you will receive positive TrueSpirit faction. (Note: Since<br>
the patch on 10/03/00, you can no longer keep handing Camin the note and gain<br>
faction.. it has been nerfed)<br>
<br>
Camin will now reply with -<br>
<br>
     Camin says, 'So you have met Solomen, eh? He is a man with a wealth<br>
     of knowledge. It is good to hear he is well.<br>
<br>
Now hail Camin and he will respond with this -<br>
<br>
     Camin says 'Go away! I have no time for you! <br>
<br>
If this happens, you can continue with the quest. (Note: Since the patch on 10/03/00,<br>
you can no longer keep handing Camin the note and gain faction.. it has been<br>
nerfed). <br>
<br>
If you have good faction already, you can talk to Camin: <br>
<br>
     you say, 'What are you searching for?'<br>
     Camin says 'Ah! A smart one, I see! If you really wish to know about<br>
     such a thing, you will have to help me finance my studies. The knowledge<br>
     I have acquired and researched did not come cheaply.<br>
<br>
At this point, hand Camin 1000 platinum and the quest will continue. Some have even<br>
reported this as working while being apprehensive to him (confirmed you must do this<br>
part of the quest or the next part will result in &quot;I do not do business with your<br>
kind.&quot;). Doing this will make Camin reply with:<br>
<br>
     Camin says, 'Good, good, you show a willingness to learn of this with<br>
     your offer. What I can tell you is that Solusek Ro had four followers who<br>
     had shown exceptional aptitude in the arts of wizardry. Solusek Ro<br>
     himself tutored them. He considered them to be like his own children. I<br>
     know of one who still exists. He goes by the name of Arantir Karondor.<br>
     He used to specialize in the storing of magic into physical objects. Arantir<br>
     has been hiding for many, many years and will most assuredly be going<br>
     by another name, so keep your eyes open. Anyway, be off, I need to<br>
     continue my research. Return to me if you ever find Arantir Karondor.'<br>
<br>
Now to find Arantir Karondor. I honestly have no idea what Verant was thinking when<br>
they did this part of the quest. There are zero clues as to who or where this person is<br>
and honestly, it's sort of disturbing to me that every other class' quest is<br>
straightforward, but still has a very good degree of difficulty. None the less, there is a<br>
female NPC vendor in Halas named 'Dargon' that sells a potion called Ro's Breath.<br>
She is located in front of the Shaman guild. Purchase this potion from Dargon for the<br>
sum of about 900pp to 1100pp depending on your faction and charisma. (**evil races<br>
be warned - you ARE KOS to surrounding NPC's. See this page for Halas Guard<br>
and Vendor info**). There is also three other known vendors in the world that sell<br>
Ro's Breath -<br>
<br>
     Female Barbarian, Marlyn McMerin (loc -3825, +1665), who is found on the<br>
     dock shops in Fironia Vie. <br>
     Female Iksar shaman vendor, Klok Scaleroot in West Cabilis. <br>
     Female coldain dwarf, Hudda, who is found within the bank inside the city of<br>
     Thurgadin. <br>
<br>
You can buy Ro's Breath from any of these vendors but you cannot return it to them.<br>
Neither of them will turn into Arantir. However, it is confirmed that you can buy Ro's<br>
Breath them, take it to Camin to be stripped of it's charge, and then take it to Dargon.<br>
Handing this potion to Dargon in Halas will make her turn into Arantir and the quest<br>
will continue.<br>
<br>
Now take this potion back to Camin in Erudin and hand it to him. He will reply with the<br>
following:<br>
<br>
     Camin says 'Very interesting... I've seen this work before. Yes, yes! It's<br>
     the work of Arantir Karondor! Give this back to the person you got it<br>
     from. Maybe he will have a clue to Arantir's location.' <br>
<br>
     Your faction standing with Truespirit got better<br>
     You gain experience!!<br>
<br>
Camin gives you back the potion (it has now been stripped of it's Shield of Lava<br>
charge) and you must take it back to Dargon in Halas.<br>
Note: you cannot skip the previous trip to Camin. You absolutely, must hand the<br>
potion to Camin. If you try to skip the trip to Erudin, you will get the following<br>
message from Dargon: &quot;I didnt request this item, but thank you very much&quot;.<br>
<br>
Back in Halas, hand the Ro's Breath potion back to Dargon. She will turn into blue robe<br>
adorned, Arantir Karondor and reply with:<br>
<br>
     Dargon says 'So, I've been discovered! You must know Camin - he is<br>
     one of the only people who could have recognized my work. I have<br>
     worked very hard to mask my presence here.' <br>
<br>
     You say, 'hail Arantir Karondor' <br>
     Arantir Karondor says 'Before I tell you anything, I require you to help<br>
     me. Seek a woman named Challice. Give her this letter and then return to<br>
     me.'<br>
<br>
The letter that Arantir hands you is actually a ring called Arantir's Ring. Identifying it<br>
reveals: &quot;Item Lore: My love has no bounds.&quot; Challice is found in the basement of the<br>
Felwithe paladin guild. NOTE: Keep in mind that Arantir will despawn in three<br>
minutes. So if you want to keep him there while you run to Felwithe, have a friend<br>
stay with Arantir and continue to talk to him until you return. It has also been<br>
noted that even trying to keep Arantir spawned by talking to him will not work<br>
for he will sometimes despawn regardless. If this happens, you must respawn him<br>
with another stripped Ro's Breath or wait for another wizard to do so. Hand<br>
Challice the ring and she will reply with:<br>
<br>
     Challice says 'Oh yes? Arantir? What a fool he was! the man gave me<br>
     everything, but for all his intelligence, he could never understand why I<br>
     was truly with him. It was for his power; he could do anything. But when<br>
     he mysteriously lost it, he became just another toy. I never loved him.<br>
     Return this ring to him. He will understand that I have no desire to see<br>
     him again.' <br>
<br>
     Your faction standing with Truespirit got better<br>
     You gain experience!!<br>
<br>
This new ring, when indentified reads: &quot;Item Lore: I never could love a man like you.&quot;<br>
Take this ring back to Arantir and hand it over (WARNING: You cannot hand the<br>
ring to Dargon if Arantir has despawned. You must hand it to Arantir. Arantir<br>
despawns about 3 minutes after speaking to him the first time so you must either<br>
be quick, wait for another wizard to make him spawn, or have a friend stay with<br>
Arantir and continue to speak to him - keeping him spawned). Then you must hail<br>
him to get his attention and go through the following dialogue:<br>
<br>
     you say, 'Hail Arantir Karondor!'<br>
     Arantir Karondor says 'Ah, but it pains my heart to see this. How I<br>
     could love a women like that is beyond me. And yet, I still do love her. It<br>
     was on the day I was to ask her to marry me that I lost my powers.<br>
     When I was about to cast my greatest spell to prove my love to her, my<br>
     magic failed. She ran out on me that day. But enough of me, do you wish<br>
     to hear my story?' <br>
<br>
     you say, 'I wish to hear your story.'<br>
     Arantir Karondor says 'I once was one of four true followers of<br>
     Solusek Ro. So great were the four of us that Solusek Ro himself made<br>
     us each a special item. We did not know what the others' items were, but<br>
     we realized that was for our own safety. Each one of us, after receiving<br>
     the item, began to plot against Solusek Ro. Each of us believed we had<br>
     enough power to dominate Norrath. Solusek Ro saw this and at the time<br>
     we needed our powers most, he stripped us of them. Now I know two of<br>
     the other wizards by name. One was called Sylen Tyrn, the other's name<br>
     was Demunir Scry. The last wizard was a gnome, but I can't think of his<br>
     name.<br>
<br>
     you say, 'What about Sylen Tyrn?'<br>
     Arantir Karondor says 'Sylen was a high elf wizard, and like many high<br>
     elves, he believed himself to be better than others. Because of his birth,<br>
     he thought he was more noble and more intelligent than anyone else. I<br>
     heard how met his demise - while flying over a vast area of water, his<br>
     powers were stripped from him in midflight. He fell and was captured by<br>
     a rival wizard who specialized in magics of the water. Search for that<br>
     wizard and you could find a trace of Sylen.<br>
<br>
The 'trace' of Sylen Tyrn is found off of Phiningel Autropos deep in Kedge Keep - the<br>
Blue Crystal Staff. When this item is identified, the power of Solusek Ro radiates from<br>
within.<br>
<br>
     you say, 'What about Demunir Scry?'<br>
     Arantir Karondor says 'Demunir was a human in a rush for power. He<br>
     was extremely intelligent and resourceful but, unfortunately, was more<br>
     interested in destructive magic. Hearing of an ancient land, he<br>
     immediately traveled to it, believing there to be powerful relics left<br>
     undiscovered there. While exploring, he came upon a dwelling that<br>
     housed a powerful warrior. Believing himself to be more powerful, he<br>
     attempted to take this dwelling for himself. While in battle with this<br>
     warrior, Solusek Ro stole his powers and left him helpless. It is said that<br>
     Demunir's item is the warrior's most prized trophy.<br>
<br>
The Demunir item is the Gnarled Staff found off of Venril Sathir from within Karnor's<br>
Castle.<br>
<br>
     you say, 'What about the gnome?'<br>
     if he doesn't reply, say the following..<br>
     you say, 'Who is the gnome?'<br>
     Arantir Karondor says 'Ah, the gnome I know very little about. I know<br>
     he was small and crafty, and that he had a brother. His brother's craft<br>
     was that of making fireworks, and he was the unfortunate victim of one<br>
     of his own experiments. His firework exploded, leaving his mind<br>
     diminished in capacity, even for a gnome. I remember others calling him<br>
     'Old Stewpot' in jest. I do not know if this is his birth name, but it may<br>
     help you to locate him. I hear he also stays close to water because of the<br>
     explosion. You never know when another gnomish invention will go awry.<br>
     Give him this letter to help motivate him to remember. <br>
<br>
The gnome is Kandin Firepot. Kandin can be found in the Southwest region of<br>
ButcherBlock Mountains (-1500 +2800) near the ocean. You can hand him the note<br>
from Arantir and he will give you the text below:<br>
<br>
     Kandin Firepot says 'Brother! I have one of those. He's great, but he's<br>
     dead. His name was Gabstik and he was a really powerful wizard. I still<br>
     have one of his greatest possesions! You look like you could use it. I've<br>
     added another thing to my shopping list. I require a dry brittle skin that I<br>
     can mold or a rare oil found in the planes that I can soak the fuse in. Get<br>
     me one of these things and I'll trade it for my bother's stick.'<br>
<br>
     Your faction standing with Truespirit got better<br>
<br>
You can do this part of the quest two ways now but it is easier to do it the new way<br>
(thank you Verant for realizing our epic quest was nearly impossible).<br>
<br>
THE FIRST WAY (the hard way) -<br>
<br>
If you have happen to have Cazic's Skin from Cazic Thule in Fear (some may have the<br>
skin from before the patch), you can hand it to Kandin and he will reply with the<br>
following -<br>
<br>
     Kandin Firepot says 'Great! This is? What is this for again? Oh yeah,<br>
     the casing for my firework. Here, you can have this then, oh no, wait.<br>
     You can't yet. I forgot I needed another part to my firework, and you are<br>
     exactly the person to get it for me! I need some mistletoe powder. Now,<br>
     go find some for me! Go, go, go, go! Shoo! Oh, wait! Hold on to my bag<br>
     for me, please. You can give it back after you've given me what I want.<br>
<br>
     Your faction standing with Truespirit got better<br>
<br>
At this point, Kandin Firepot will give you 'Kandin's Bag'. When identified, the bag<br>
comes up with: Item Lore: Warning - Explosive!&quot;. Although it is a bag, it cannot be<br>
opened. Don't worry about this, continue with the quest.<br>
<br>
The mistletoe powder is found within Old Sebilis upon Tolapmulj. Once you have the<br>
powder, return to Kandin and hand only the powder to him. Upon handing Kandin the<br>
mistletoe powder, he will return to you the Staff of Gabstik. Once he hands you the<br>
staff he asks for his bag back. Hand him 'Kandin's Bag' -<br>
<br>
     Kandin Firepot says 'Great! Give this to Arantir so he knows you've<br>
     helped me! Hey! Have you seen my lantern anywhere? <br>
<br>
     Your faction standing with Truespirit got better<br>
<br>
THE SECOND WAY (the new way) -<br>
<br>
If you hail Kandin instead of handing him the skin, the following is what will happen -<br>
<br>
     You say, 'hail Kandin Firepot'<br>
<br>
     Kandin Firepot says 'Hello, there! Don't have time to talk. I'm workin',<br>
     workin', workin'! Careful! Don't slip in the oil! <br>
<br>
     You say, 'what oil?'<br>
<br>
     Kandin Firepot says 'Ah the oil! I recently sent a specially crafted<br>
     golem to explore through a huge portal to another plane. It's instructions<br>
     were to collect special oil that I suspect existed in the plane. What I think<br>
     is the golem broke down. This looks like a good task for one like you. Go<br>
     see what's wrong with the golem. Here is spare gears of mine incase it's<br>
     broken. Be careful though, if you put it in wrong it could explode or<br>
     worse! <br>
<br>
This golem is a non-aggro 'broken golem' that is found in the Plane of Fear. Hand the<br>
broken golem the golem sprocket -<br>
<br>
     an enraged golem says 'Error! Malfunction! Destroy! <br>
     an enraged golem says 'Warriors like you always bring out the worst in<br>
     me.'<br>
<br>
You now have an enraged golem on your hands that is aggro. The enraged golem can<br>
double hit for 400 each, has approximately 150k HP and is not a caster. Flame based<br>
spells and lures are most efficient to use in bringing him down. Once he is dead, loot<br>
the green oil from his corpse. Take this green oil back to Kandin in the ButcherBlock<br>
Mountains.<br>
<br>
     You say, 'hail Kandin Firepot'<br>
<br>
     Kandin Firepot says 'Hello, there! Don't have time to talk. I'm workin',<br>
     workin', workin'! Careful! Don't slip in the oil!<br>
<br>
Hand over the oil -<br>
<br>
     Kandin Firepot says 'Oh wow! You found the oil! Where is the golem?<br>
     You didn't hurt him did you? I am very fond of him. Anyways, here is<br>
     your reward a note and staff to give to that guy you were asking me<br>
     about. <br>
<br>
     Your faction standing with Truespirit got better<br>
<br>
You will now have BOTH the note to take to Arantir and the Staff of Gabstik.<br>
